triples.evidence: At that moment, all the spins point together again, aligned in the same direction. Because they are all aligned, their contributions add up constructively, and the transverse magnetization reaches its maximum. This produces a measurable signal in the nearby coils - the spin echo signal.

concepts.term: The black spins are inherently faster, so even though they were moved behind, they continue to process quickly.
